I'm sorry.

21:06.932 --> 21:07.766
It's okay.

21:08.392 --> 21:10.894
Admittedly,
this is all way more complicated

21:10.978 --> 21:13.605
-than any of us could have planned.

21:13.689 --> 21:16.566
You and me, for example.
I'm your best guy-friend.

21:16.650 --> 21:19.820
Betty is your best girl-friend.
Your best friends are dating.

21:20.445 --> 21:22.656
But B and V are also best friends,

21:22.739 --> 21:26.952
so, your best friend's girlfriend is
also your girlfriend's best friend.

21:27.035 --> 21:30.622
-Uh, no. Not really.

21:30.706 --> 21:34.751
It should be amazing we're all so close.
But sometimes it terrifies me.

21:37.045 --> 21:39.089
It's like the four of us are
in a powder keg.

21:39.965 --> 21:42.634
All it would take is one match,
and we'd all blow up.

21:49.266 --> 21:50.726
Great toss, Archie.

21:53.186 --> 21:57.024
I'm glad you called, Josie.
I was thinking about this year's musical,

21:57.107 --> 22:00.819
which I'm directing, and I want it
to be a star vehicle for you.

22:01.194 --> 22:05.115
You might not want that
after I tell you why I called.

22:06.116 --> 22:09.161
What are you doing here?

22:10.203 --> 22:12.873
-So, it's true.

22:12.956 --> 22:17.044
Mom's risking her life every single day,
and you're running around with your boss.

22:17.711 --> 22:18.587
Former boss.

22:19.171 --> 22:22.674
God. I spent my whole life
trying to live up to your standards.

22:22.758 --> 22:24.509
-Kevin--
-And it's all crap.

22:29.639 --> 22:33.435
So, Betty, unless that was some
seriously aggressive hand-holding

22:33.518 --> 22:36.063
-I heard through the wall last night...

22:36.146 --> 22:37.272
When did that start?

22:38.815 --> 22:40.942
The night of your confirmation.

22:41.777 --> 22:43.028
-Mm-hm.

22:43.570 --> 22:48.408
Well, as my <i>abuelita</i> likes to say,
"Praise Jesus."

22:48.784 --> 22:53.080
Hi. I'd like this, and this.

22:53.747 --> 22:57.751
And-- Oh, the last time I was here,
you had the most scrumptious scones.

22:57.834 --> 23:00.629
Yeah, my grandma makes them,
but just during the summer.

23:00.712 --> 23:04.007
-For the summer people.
-Oh. That's when we normally come up.

23:04.091 --> 23:06.259
Ah. Thought I recognized you.

23:06.343 --> 23:08.345
You got one of those places
on Shadow Lake.

23:08.845 --> 23:12.265
-But you're usually with your folks.
-Yeah, they're back in, um...

23:12.933 --> 23:14.309
I was about to say New York,

23:14.392 --> 23:16.520
-but we're in Riverdale now.

23:16.603 --> 23:19.147
Bet they don't even know
what to do with you there.

23:19.231 --> 23:20.607
No, they do not.

23:21.149 --> 23:24.027
-Enough flirting here.

23:24.111 --> 23:27.030
You had a fight with Archie,
you didn't break up with him.

23:27.864 --> 23:28.949
I'm Cassidy.

23:37.165 --> 23:39.835
So, how's it been

23:40.460 --> 23:43.964
-Oh. Things have been nice.

23:44.297 --> 23:46.341
Nice is not what I heard last night.

23:46.424 --> 23:50.804
Okay, you know what I wore that night
we got Chuck into that hot tub?

23:51.388 --> 23:52.472
Betty, what

23:55.809 --> 23:57.310
Hi.

23:58.145 --> 23:59.437
Hey.

24:05.694 --> 24:07.112
Are you still mad at me?

24:07.696 --> 24:08.572
Yes.

24:10.157 --> 24:13.160
But you can make it up to me
by remembering one thing.

24:13.243 --> 24:15.495
And it's simple and non-negotiable.

24:16.913 --> 24:22.002
From now on, it's me and you,
not you and my dad, okay?

24:27.674 --> 24:31.344
If that's Cheryl, tell her everyone
kissed everyone and it's over.

24:31.428 --> 24:32.262
It's my dad.

24:33.471 --> 24:34.806
Hey. Dad, what's up?

24:34.890 --> 24:37.309
<i>Jughead, hey.</i>
<i>You're not gonna believe it.</i>

24:37.392 --> 24:39.895
Hold on. I can't hear you. Hold on a sec.

24:39.978 --> 24:41.855
Everyone's over here celebrating.

24:41.938 --> 24:44.524
Listen. The eviction notices,
the back rent,

24:44.608 --> 24:47.485
it's all gone, paid in full.
No one has to move out.

24:47.569 --> 24:51.198
-You. You shamed him into it.

24:51.281 --> 24:52.741
<i>He did a complete 180.</i>

24:53.366 --> 24:56.953
What are you talking about?
-Hiram. Hiram Lodge.

24:57.037 --> 25:01.124
Well, he just bought Sunnyside
Trailer Park and he said we can all stay.

25:01.208 --> 25:03.293
-We're staying!

25:04.628 --> 25:05.462
<i>Jug.</i> <i>Jug.</i>

25:20.060 --> 25:24.689
First your dad buys the drive-in,
now he owns Sunnyside Trailer Park.

25:24.773 --> 25:28.318
As I suspected, he is gobbling up
the Southside, piece by piece.

25:28.401 --> 25:31.321
Slow down. Mr. Lodge is evicting people
from the trailer park?

25:31.863 --> 25:34.991
No, he cleared us of our debts
and revoked our evictions.

25:35.075 --> 25:37.577
-Yes.

25:37.827 --> 25:40.747
-Because it's a tactic.

25:40.830 --> 25:44.626
It's a smokescreen. PR 101.
He's trying to buy my silence again.

25:44.709 --> 25:47.587
Good lord, Jughead.
How much of a narcissist are you?

25:47.671 --> 25:50.924
You wrote an article attacking Mr. Lodge,

25:51.007 --> 25:53.635
demanding he makes amends.
That's what he's trying to do.

25:55.345 --> 25:57.055
They do kind of have a point.

25:57.639 --> 26:00.433
Look, Jug, I know you love conspiracies,

26:01.184 --> 26:03.561
but take the win, bro,
and let's celebrate.

26:04.562 --> 26:08.984
I credit you with a lot of things, Josie,
but being cruel is not one of them.

26:10.235 --> 26:14.197
-Tom told me what you said to Kevin.
-He deserved to know the truth.

26:14.281 --> 26:16.866
So, maybe he could save
his parents' marriage.

26:16.950 --> 26:20.370
Kevin's not talking to his father.
Tom's trying to reach his wife.

26:20.453 --> 26:22.706
-It's a mess.
-Like what you did to us.

26:22.789 --> 26:26.042
Imploding our lives?
Without even telling me?

26:26.126 --> 26:29.587
I did not implode our lives.
The Lodges did.

26:29.671 --> 26:33.925
It's not how I wanted things to come out,
that choice was taken away from me.

26:34.009 --> 26:37.387
Just like you took it away
from Tom and Kevin.

26:39.180 --> 26:40.890
I wasn't trying to hurt them.

26:41.474 --> 26:43.727
And I wasn't trying to hurt you, either.

26:59.409 --> 27:01.494
Kevin. Hey.

27:02.245 --> 27:04.873
-Hey, Moose, Midge.

27:05.498 --> 27:06.333
Nope.

27:06.958 --> 27:08.168
Uh, I'm alone.

27:10.211 --> 27:12.714
In that case, grab your plate
and come sit with us.

27:14.132 --> 27:16.676
-Yeah, definitely.

27:17.802 --> 27:19.012
The more the merrier.

27:20.513 --> 27:21.639
Why the hell not?

27:23.600 --> 27:28.188
So, Kevin, who are you meeting
at the movie

27:28.730 --> 27:33.485
Oh, no, I don't have a date.
I'm just going to this gay rom-com alone.

27:34.319 --> 27:35.153
What?

27:36.446 --> 27:39.324
No. No, that's crazy.
We need to find you someone.

27:40.200 --> 27:44.204
What about one of those new
Southside guys? I hear one of them's gay.

27:44.287 --> 27:47.374
If it's Fangs Fogarty, I don't think
I can date someone named Fangs.

27:47.457 --> 27:49.834
-He's a good-looking dude.
Oh, my God.

27:49.918 --> 27:52.253
Please. What do you know, you big lug?

27:57.926 --> 28:01.471
Hey, so, how did you two, uh,
get to be friends, anyway?

28:02.138 --> 28:04.849
-Uh... We, um...

28:06.935 --> 28:08.728
-We were...
Mm-hm.

28:09.312 --> 28:10.522
Lab partners.

28:10.897 --> 28:11.773
Biology.

28:12.899 --> 28:13.733
Oh. Hm.

28:25.370 --> 28:27.330
<i>âª Cold, cold blood âª</i>

28:35.380 --> 28:37.465
<i>âª Cold, cold blood âª</i>

28:51.354 --> 28:53.022
<i>âª Cold blood âª</i>

28:54.691 --> 28:55.525
Kevin?

28:57.318 --> 28:58.153
Josie.

28:59.362 --> 29:02.657
Here to tell me more bad news?
I don't think I could take that.

29:02.741 --> 29:06.453
No, no. I had to get out of the house.

29:06.536 --> 29:08.204
So, I came here. Heh.

29:08.788 --> 29:10.874
And I saw you and, um...

29:11.624 --> 29:14.002
I'm sorry about what I said.

29:14.461 --> 29:15.295
I--

29:15.879 --> 29:20.633
It wasn't my place to do that.
I was just hurting and mad at my mom--

29:20.717 --> 29:22.427
It's okay, Josie.

29:24.095 --> 29:25.013
Um...

29:25.680 --> 29:27.724
You Are you here with somebody?

29:32.187 --> 29:36.775
Let me guess,
some cherry cola for Cheryl Bombshell.

29:37.358 --> 29:40.945
Oh, my God. What do you want?
And why do you keep stalking me?

29:41.029 --> 29:42.071
I'm not.

29:42.155 --> 29:45.283
I came to see this movie with Fangs
and he bailed on me.

29:48.495 --> 29:49.537
Are you okay?

29:51.206 --> 29:52.707
I'm alone at the movies.

29:53.374 --> 29:55.752
And I'm trying to stay away from my mother

29:55.835 --> 29:58.546
who has turned our house
into her sexual playpen.

30:00.548 --> 30:01.382
So, no.

30:02.717 --> 30:03.760
I am really not.

30:04.302 --> 30:08.389
Well, I was gonna go grab a seat alone,

30:08.473 --> 30:12.644
unless you want some company,
but no pressure.

30:18.858 --> 30:21.694
<i>But these last few years,</i>

30:21.778 --> 30:24.447
<i>it's almost like I could feel you</i>
<i>holding your breath.</i>

30:25.740 --> 30:28.451
<i>You are still you, Simon.</i>

30:29.536 --> 30:34.123
<i>You get to be more you</i>
<i>than you have been in a very long time.</i>

30:34.707 --> 30:36.709
<i>You deserve everything you want.</i>

30:37.710 --> 30:40.255
I have a hotel on Park Place.
Okay.

30:40.338 --> 30:43.716
Which brings your total to $1500.

30:44.217 --> 30:46.135
Sorry, B. It's nothing personal.

30:46.219 --> 30:48.346
Yeah, I know. It's just business.

30:48.429 --> 30:49.430
Mm-hm.

30:52.934 --> 30:54.143
Ew, it's my mom.

30:54.561 --> 30:55.979
-No.

30:56.062 --> 30:57.272
-No.
-No.

30:57.355 --> 30:59.315
What if it's about Chic? Let me just--

31:00.733 --> 31:02.110
Hey, Mom, what's up?

31:02.694 --> 31:06.406
By the way, when are we ever gonna get
to meet Chic?

31:06.489 --> 31:08.449
I actually did, before we left. And

31:12.328 --> 31:14.163
Honestly, he's kind of creepy.

31:14.747 --> 31:16.958
Guys.

31:17.041 --> 31:18.376
No, actually.

31:19.586 --> 31:25.466
My mom is freaking out because Hiram Lodge
just bought the <i>Riverdale Register</i>.

31:34.309 --> 31:37.687
My mom is losing her mind,
my dad's not answering her calls.

31:37.770 --> 31:39.022
Veronica, did you know

31:39.105 --> 31:42.483

No, Betty, of course not.

31:42.567 --> 31:45.028
-This is what I'm talking about.
-Relax, Jughead.

31:45.111 --> 31:47.822
-Don't tell me to relax.

31:47.906 --> 31:49.908
To get us out of town
while your dad does these things?

31:49.991 --> 31:51.868
Okay, now who sounds crazy?

31:51.951 --> 31:55.663
Lodge Industries has been buying
properties all over the Southside.

31:55.747 --> 31:59.959
Now he buys the town's newspaper
so people can't report on what he's doing?

32:00.043 --> 32:02.170
This is a classic gambit of criminals.

32:02.253 --> 32:04.797
-Shut up, Jughead.
-Archie, this one's simple.

32:04.881 --> 32:09.052
Even you might get this if you stopped
kissing up to Hiram for two seconds.

32:09.135 --> 32:13.556
How many times have I defended you?
And now you stab my family in the back?

32:13.640 --> 32:18.144
It sounds to me you should be mad at
your dad for selling the paper, not mine.

32:18.227 --> 32:21.189
And there's nothing evil
about buying a newspaper.

32:21.272 --> 32:25.151
He's trying to silence the free press,
keep Mrs. Cooper from coming after him.

32:25.234 --> 32:27.987
I am so sick of your vendetta
against my dad.

32:28.071 --> 32:32.367
-He's done plenty of good things.
Name one thing.

32:32.450 --> 32:34.953
-He's--
-He paid my dad's medical bills.

32:35.036 --> 32:38.039
Boy, Archie. Veronica's got you
wrapped around her little finger.

32:38.122 --> 32:39.624
And other parts of her body.

32:39.707 --> 32:42.126
Oh! I'm sorry.

32:42.210 --> 32:46.089
I'm sorry we don't spend our time being
tragic, and moping, and holding hands

32:46.172 --> 32:48.341
while watching
serial-killer documentaries.

32:48.424 --> 32:51.094
And wearing costumes to role-play
to get our rocks off.

32:55.598 --> 32:58.059
-Oh, my God.

32:58.142 --> 32:59.936
You rich folks never learn.

33:00.019 --> 33:04.107
You just keep walking around town,
flashing cash than we see in a year.

33:04.190 --> 33:06.776
We're gonna take what we want,
and then go,

33:06.859 --> 33:10.154
and if you guys behave yourselves,
nobody gets their skulls knocked in.

33:12.782 --> 33:15.868
Fine. Take what you want.
We won't give you any trouble.

33:15.952 --> 33:17.161
Where's your purse?

33:18.162 --> 33:19.622
Um, it's...

33:21.124 --> 33:21.958
In my bedroom.

33:22.709 --> 33:26.462
-Let's go to the bedroom.
-No. No way are you going with her alone.

33:26.546 --> 33:28.339
-I'll go.
Archie.

33:29.507 --> 33:31.759
It's fine. I'll be fine.

33:32.343 --> 33:33.511
We'll be right back.

33:34.053 --> 33:35.805
Everybody just needs to stay calm.

33:46.691 --> 33:47.608
It's over there.

33:48.735 --> 33:50.945
I'm just gonna pick it up, okay?

34:02.165 --> 34:03.499
Why are you doing this?

34:11.841 --> 34:13.342
You think I don't recognize you?

34:14.385 --> 34:16.804
-Shut up and get your wallet.

34:40.953 --> 34:42.914
Can we go already

34:42.997 --> 34:44.957
Yeah. I got the cash.

34:45.041 --> 34:47.710
-Then you got what you wanted.
-Not everything.

34:48.419 --> 34:51.214
Not yet. Why don't you all get down
on your knees?

34:51.756 --> 34:54.509
-Come on, man. Let's not do this.
-Shut up.

34:54.592 --> 34:56.636
I said, on your knees.

34:57.178 --> 34:58.930
Hands behind your backs.

34:59.514 --> 35:00.473
Do it!

35:15.071 --> 35:16.364
It's a nice cabin.

35:17.657 --> 35:19.408
Sorry we have to make such a mess in it.

35:22.120 --> 35:23.121
The hell is that?

35:23.788 --> 35:28.334
That would be the security company calling
to check on the alarm I hit in my bedroom.

35:28.417 --> 35:32.839
I'd say you have 30 seconds to run
before this place is swarming with guards

35:32.922 --> 35:35.007
who will shoot first
and ask questions never.

35:39.846 --> 35:41.848
Screw you, rich bitch.

35:44.308 --> 35:46.144
Archie, don't!
No, Arch!

36:03.786 --> 36:07.707
Andre. There were some other guys
with him. Did you see them?

36:07.790 --> 36:10.543
Go back to the cabin.
I'll take care it from here.

36:11.836 --> 36:13.588
-I said...

36:14.297 --> 36:15.506
I'll take care of it.

36:46.537 --> 36:50.374
First of all, thank you, Mom,
and Sheriff Keller,

36:50.458 --> 36:52.585
for coming to meet me and Kevin.

36:52.668 --> 36:55.671
-We promise you this isn't a trap.
-It's that--

36:56.422 --> 37:00.384
Kevin and I were talking
after the movie and we thought--

37:00.843 --> 37:03.095
This conversation is bigger
than just two people.

37:03.763 --> 37:06.224
It's bigger than the people
in this booth, even.

37:06.807 --> 37:09.101
And it's probably gonna be a long one.

37:09.185 --> 37:12.980
So, we should get started.

37:23.908 --> 37:26.911
You may think you've mastered
the art of silent tears,

37:26.994 --> 37:31.123
-but I saw you crying during that movie.
-I never cry at movies.

37:31.207 --> 37:32.959
Real life's tragic enough.

37:34.252 --> 37:36.921
But when Simon's mom said

37:37.004 --> 37:39.590
he used to be such a carefree kid
growing up,

37:40.258 --> 37:45.471
and then, at a certain point,
he stopped being that happy kid,

37:45.930 --> 37:49.058
-because he was hiding a secret, it just--
-Cheryl.

37:51.102 --> 37:54.438
Everyone thinks I'm this loveless monster.

37:55.523 --> 37:56.816
But it isn't true.

37:59.610 --> 38:01.070
I loved someone...

38:02.488 --> 38:03.656
who loved me.

38:05.825 --> 38:07.368
And my mother destroyed it.

38:08.160 --> 38:09.745
You mean your brother Jason?

38:11.580 --> 38:13.374
I heard how close you guys were.

38:14.083 --> 38:16.127
No. Not Jay-Jay.

38:17.795 --> 38:18.629
Her...

38:19.338 --> 38:22.258
Her name was Heather.

38:27.013 --> 38:29.307
She was my best friend in junior high.

38:30.474 --> 38:32.852
She used to sleep over every weekend.

38:33.853 --> 38:37.523
Until one night, my mother caught us
in the same bed.

38:38.566 --> 38:41.652
She said I was deviant.

38:42.945 --> 38:44.905
Cheryl, I am so sorry.

38:45.906 --> 38:48.242
But you have to know your mother's wrong.

38:49.201 --> 38:51.037
You're not loveless.

38:51.120 --> 38:53.664
You're not deviant, okay?

38:56.417 --> 38:59.045
You're sensational.

39:02.089 --> 39:06.677
